This topic describes how to install and configure Azuqua Platform Connector for PCF.

##<a id='install'></a> Install via Pivotal Ops Manager

1. Download the product file from [Pivotal Network](https://network.pivotal.io/).

1. Upload the product file to your Ops Manager installation.

2. Navigate to "Available Products" view in the Ops Manager and click **Add** next to the uploaded product description to add Azuqua to your staging area.

3. Click the newly added tile to review any configurable options.

4. Populate the configuration options for your Azuqua accountâ€™s Access Key and Secret

![Azuqua for PCF Tile: Azuqua Access Keys pane](azuqua-config-keys.png)

5. Click **Apply Changes** to install the service.

6. Once deployed, visit the URL for the web dashboard. By default this will be <https://azuqua.my-pcf.com>.

##<a id='configure'></a>Configure the Azuqua Tile 

1. On completion of Azuqua tile install, check Services Marketplace in Apps Manager

2. View Azuqua Service Plans.

3. Bind the Azuqua Service to an Application.

4. Check the service or dashboard for the partner for more data.

